TASK: implement_module

TARGET: src/modules

CREATE: ExampleModule

PURPOSE: [describe what this module does in one sentence]

EXTENDS: BaseModule

IMPLEMENTS:
- Configurable
- Disposable

PARAMS:
- config: ModuleConfig
- logger: Logger

PUBLIC_METHODS:
- initialize() — set up resources
- process(input: Input) — process a single input item
- shutdown() — clean up resources

BEHAVIOR:
- initialize() creates internal state from config
- process() validates input, transforms it, returns result
- shutdown() flushes buffers and releases handles
- all errors are caught and logged, not thrown

OVERRIDES:
- getName() — return module identifier

CONSTRAINTS:
- follow lint rules
- follow neighboring module style
- no new abstractions
- no refactoring existing code
- no unrelated edits
- no external dependencies

DONE_WHEN:
- lint passes
- types pass
- exports added to index
- module can be instantiated with mock dependencies
